definition.value: A data region point is a data point that is a member of a data region. [Allotrope]
A data region start point is the data point of the region with the smallest abscissa value. [Allotrope]
A data region end point is the data point of the region with the largest abscissa value. [Allotrope]
An osmolality aggregate document is a document that aggregates osmolality documents. [Allotrope]
An osmolality document is a document that encompasses the information associated with an osmolality run. [Allotrope]
A weighing aggregate document is a document that aggregates weighing documents. [Allotrope]
A weighing document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a weighing. [Allotrope]
An electronic signature aggregate document is a document that aggregates electronic signature documents. [Allotrope]
A chromatography column separation mode is a classification datum that classifies a column by the type of chromatography it supports. [Allotrope]
A stationary phase document is a document that encapsulates the information associated with a stationary phase. [Allotrope]
A substrate document is a document that encapsulates the information associated with a substrate. [Allotrope]
A substrate permeability type is a classification datum that classifies the permeability of a substrate. [Allotrope]
A substrate material description is a description of the material used in a substrate. [Allotrope]
A phase chemistry type is a classification datum that classifies the chemistry of some stationary phase. [Allotrope]
An acidity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the acidity of a chromatographic stationary phase. [Allotrope]
A basicity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the basicity of a chromatographic stationary phase. [Allotrope]
A hydrophobicity is a quality quantification facet that quantifies the hydrophobicity of a chromatographic stationary phase. [Allotrope]
A steric resistance is the quality quantification facet that quantifies the steric resistance of a chromatographic stationary phase. [Allotrope]
A polarizability is the quality quantification facet that quantifies the polarizability of a chromatographic stationary phase. [Allotrope]
An automated reactor aggregate document is a document that aggregates automated reactor documents. [Allotrope]
An automated reactor document is a document that encompasses the information associated with an automated reactor run. [Allotrope]
A capability aggregate document is a document that aggregates capability documents. [Allotrope]
A capability document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some capability. [Allotrope]

A capability feature is a facet that defines the feature with the role of a description or classification of a property, characteristic or facet of some data with the role of specified capability. [Allotrope]
A number of scans setting is a setting that specifies the number of scans scans that are taken as part of or aggregated into a single measurement. [Allotrope]

A multi-dimensional nuclear magnetic resonance spectrum is a spectrum with multiple dimensions that shows the response of spin-active nuclei to radio frequency radiation in an applied magnetic field. [CHMO]

A multi-dimensional free induction decay spectrum is a nuclear magnetic resonance spectrum with multiple dimensions that quantifies the combined decay of aligned nuclear spins after excitation with a short radio-frequency pulse (data before the Fourier transform to the frequency domain. [Allotrope]
An analysis sequence document is a document that encompasses the information associated with an analysis sequence. [Allotrope]
A data region aggregate aggregate document is a document that aggregates data region documents. [Allotrope]
A data region document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a data region. [Allotrope]
A distribution aggregate document is a document that aggregates distribution documents. [Allotrope]
A distribution identifier is an identifier that identifies some distribution. [Allotrope]
A rheometry aggregate document is a document that aggregates rheometry documents. [Allotrope]
A rheometry document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a rheometry run. [Allotrope]
A measurement chamber document is a document that encapsulates the information associated with a measurement chamber. [Allotrope]
A measurement chamber type is a classification datum that classifies some measurement chamber. [Allotrope]
A gap length is a length that quantifies the length of some gap between two surfaces. [Allotrope]
A radius is a quality quantification facet that quantifies some radius. [Allotrope]
A cup radius is a radius that quantifies the radius of some cup. [Allotrope]
A bob radius is a radius that quantifies the radius of some bob. [Allotrope]
A truncation is a length that quantifies the gap between the tip of a cone and a flat surface in a rheometry experiment. [Allotrope]
A rheometry data cube is a data cube that is a representation of a rheometry curve. [Allotrope]
A rheometry curve is a data distribution function that is the plot of the rheological properties of some fluid. [Allotrope]
A peak type is a classification datum that classifies a peak by the role played by the substance it is a proxy for in some process. [Allotrope]
A electronic spectrometry aggregate document is a document that aggregates electronic spectrometry documents. [Allotrope]
A electronic spectrometry document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some electronic spectrometry run. [Allotrope]
Analyst is the role of a person which is an agent in the process of examination. [Allotrope]
Condition role is a contextual role of an information object that specifies a prerequisite. [Allotrope]
Controller role is a controlling role of some material entity that is controlling some other object or a process. [Allotrope]
Denominator is the conceptual role of a scalar that indicates the number of equal parts into which the unit is divided. [Allotrope]
